		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So is it possible the game shoves sound samples into the WRAM?</div>
<br />Very few mappers can map RAM into CPU $C000-$FFF1, the usable range that channel 5 can address. I've never seen the MMC3 do that.*
<br />
<br />
<br /><span style="font-size: 84%; line-height: normal">* Except in the case of a RAM-based copier that I own, which doesn't really count because the RAM used for PRG ROM data is write-protected by the time the game starts.</span>

		

