	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />1) You can get a different SRAM chip, which initializes the memory to 0 (which is probably what all these "faster" RAM chips did)
<br />2) Or you can grab an IPS patch <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=84526#84526" class="postlink">here</a> that should fix the RAM initialization issue. Further on in the same thread there's another patch that can be directly applied to SMB3 ROM.

		

		</td>
